gemini -p "Write Chapter 1: The NEC Mindset. Focus on the shift from rote memorization of NEC rules to a deep understanding of the 'why' behind the code. Explain how this mindset helps electricians solve real-world problems in commercial settings that aren't explicitly covered in the book." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 01 - The NEC Mindset.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 2: Navigating the NEC for the Field. Create a practical guide on how to quickly find information in the NEC. Cover the code's structure, indexing, and how to use cross-references between articles effectively. Provide a scenario-based example, like finding the requirements for a commercial rooftop HVAC unit." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 02 - Navigating the NEC.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 3: Core Commercial Power Systems. Detail the NEC requirements for services, feeders, and branch circuits in a typical commercial building. Use a 2000A, 480/277V service as a running example. Cover Articles 210, 215, 225, and 230." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 03 - Core Commercial Power Systems.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 4: Conductor Sizing and Protection in Practice. Explain how to size conductors based on real-world commercial factors like ambient temperature, conductor bundling, and voltage drop. Provide practical examples of applying Article 240 for overcurrent protection and Article 310 for ampacity." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 04 - Conductor Sizing and Protection.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 5: Raceway and Box Fill Strategies. Go beyond simple calculations. Discuss strategies for selecting the right raceway and box sizes in complex commercial environments, considering future expansion and ease of pulling wire. Reference Chapter 9 tables with practical examples." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 05 - Raceway and Box Fill.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 6: Grounding and Bonding That Works. Explain the critical safety role of grounding and bonding in commercial systems as defined in Article 250. Use diagrams and field scenarios to illustrate concepts like grounding electrode systems, equipment grounding conductors, and bonding jumpers." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 06 - Grounding and Bonding.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 7: Decoding Motor Installations. Simplify Article 430 for field application. Cover the requirements for motor circuit conductors, overload protection, disconnects, and controllers for common commercial motors (e.g., HVAC units, elevators)." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 07 - Motor Installations.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 8: Modern Commercial Lighting. Discuss NEC requirements for installing and controlling modern lighting systems, including LED fixtures and networked lighting controls. Cover load calculations (Article 220) and fixture installation (Article 410)." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 08 - Commercial Lighting.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 9: Transformer Rules for the Field. Provide a practical guide to installing transformers in commercial settings per Article 450. Cover sizing, overcurrent protection for both primary and secondary, and proper grounding and bonding." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 09 - Transformer Applications.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 10: Special Occupancies and Environments. Focus on two common commercial scenarios: hazardous locations (Article 500) and healthcare facilities (Article 517). Highlight the key differences in wiring methods and safety precautions required." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 10 - Special Occupancies.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 11: Emergency and Standby Systems. Explain the differences and NEC requirements for emergency (Article 700), legally required standby (Article 701), and optional standby (Article 702) systems. Focus on practical installation aspects of transfer switches and generators in commercial buildings." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 11 - Emergency and Standby Systems.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 12: From Blueprints to Final Inspection. Detail the process of translating electrical plans into a code-compliant installation. Provide a checklist for preparing for an electrical inspection, anticipating common points of failure, and effectively communicating with inspectors." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 12 - Plan Reading and Inspection Readiness.md"
gemini -p "Write Chapter 13: Staying Ahead of Code Changes. Discuss the NEC update cycle and provide strategies for electricians to stay current. Explain how to identify major changes in new editions and apply them correctly in the field, with examples from a recent NEC cycle." > "NEC Mastery - Ch 13 - Staying Current with Code Changes.md"